ding <code>~/.bazelrc</code>. This is undocumented, and probably should not happen. For now, the solution is copy your own bazelrc into the tensorflow root before configuring - fortunately <code>./configure</code> will not overwrite it and only append to it.</p>", "body_text": "The ./configure script will write to a .bazelrc file in the cwd to save some of it's options (in particular, jemalloc). Unfortunately this has the effect of overriding ~/.bazelrc. This is undocumented, and probably should not happen. For now, the solution is copy your own bazelrc into the tensorflow root before configuring - fortunately ./configure will not overwrite it and only append to it.", "body": "The `./configure` script will write to a `.bazelrc` file in the cwd to save some of it's options (in particular, jemalloc). Unfortunately this has the effect of overriding `~/.bazelrc`. This is undocumented, and probably should not happen. For now, the solution is copy your own bazelrc into the tensorflow root before configuring - fortunately `./configure` will not overwrite it and only append to it."}